2004-12-04  rocky <rocky>

	* src/cd-info.c: Add cast to remove compiler warning.

2004-12-04  rocky <rocky>

	* lib/_cdio_linux.c: Justin B Ruggles <jruggle@earthlink.net>
	reports:   GNU/Linux ioctl(.., CDROM_DISC_STATUS does not return "CD DATA
	  Form 2" for SVCD's when I know they are form 2, so we read a FULL
	  TOC in an attempt to make it more accurate.  Most of the info was
	  obtained the SCSI MMC draft spec revision 10a from   http://www.t10.org/ftp/t10/drafts/mmc/mmc-r10a.pdf   Pages 56 to 62 give more details.  Libcdio does not have CD-i as a   discmode, so I just have it treat CD-i as if it is CD-XA.  This doesn't work for the SVCD I tried but it is probably a step in
	the right direction. And when things settle down, it should be done
	on other OS drivers as well.

